🚀 Flow to Deploy a Static Website on Amazon S3
Sign in to AWS Console

Go to https://aws.amazon.com/console and log in.

Create an S3 Bucket

Open the S3 service.

Click on “Create bucket”.

Give it a unique name (e.g., my-static-site).

Choose the region and keep all other settings as default or adjust as needed.

Uncheck Block all public access (you’ll be warned — proceed if you're okay making it public).

Click Create bucket.

Enable Static Website Hosting

Go to the Properties tab of your bucket.

Scroll to Static website hosting.

Enable it and choose “Host a static website”.

Set the index document (e.g., index.html), and optionally an error document (e.g., error.html).

Save changes.

Upload Website Files

Go to the Objects tab.

Click Upload > Add files.

Select your index.html, style.css, script.js, etc.

Click Upload.

Make Files Public

Select all files you uploaded.

Click Actions > Make public (or use a Bucket Policy to allow public read access).

Access the Website

Go back to the Static website hosting section in Properties.

Copy the S3 endpoint URL (something like http://my-static-site.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com).

Paste it in a browser — your static website is live!

